To prove that the power sets of two equinumerable sets are equinumerable, we can leverage the fact that the power set of a set is in bijection with the set of all binary sequences of the same cardinality as the original set. Since the original sets are equinumerable, their binary sequences sets will also be equinumerable, and hence their power sets will be equinumerable.

