The Lean library already has a lemma for this! The powerset of a set is equinumerable to the set itself, and if two sets are equinumerable, their powersets are too. 

We can prove this directly using the fact that the powerset of a set is in bijection with the set of functions from the set to {0, 1}. 

For a set A, the powerset is in bijection with the set of characteristic functions from A to {0, 1}. This is a standard result in set theory. 

